

delta lake -- (ADLS gen2):  
1. its build on top of apache spark and cloud objects like azure,aws,gcp -- developed by databricks
2. basically its a storage which can store all type data
3. it support ACID property, Time travelling, schema enforcement[fail is schema missmatch]
4. unified batch ans streaming
5. it efficiently handles millions of files using a transaction log[_delta_log]

ACID transaction
A - Atomicity - untill the transaction completed fully data will not been moved, -- completely roll back if any error occur
C - consistency - enforces schema constant, which present bad data from being inserted
I - isolation - multiple user can read/write at same time
D - Durability - once the transaction is completed data is permentally stored

data objects in databricks

        METASTORE --> CATALOG --> SCHEMA -->TABLES/VIEWS/FUNCTION

tables --   
        1. managed table = table created in internal storage[metastore storage --> when metastore created admin has been given a default location-- this is where managed table data will be stored]
            CREATE TABLE database_name.table_name (
            id INT,
            name STRING
            )
            USING DELTA;
        2. external table -- table data store in external loaction 
            CREATE TABLE database_name.table_name (
            id INT,
            name STRING
            )
            USING DELTA
            LOCATION '/mnt/adls/path/to/data/';

views -- 
        1. Standard View- Standard views are permanent and stored in the metastore
            CREATE VIEW view_name AS
            SELECT * FROM table_name;
        2. Temporary View - temporary views are session-specific, if session closed in the notebook view will not be available
            CREATE TEMP VIEW temp_view_name AS
            SELECT * FROM table_name;
        3. Global Temporary View - Accessible across multiple notebooks/sessions, Stored in global_temp database
            CREATE GLOBAL TEMP VIEW global_view_name AS
            SELECT * FROM table_name;
            📌 Access it like:
            SELECT * FROM global_temp.global_view_name;

MEDALLION ARCHECTURE- 

        SOURCE --> BRONZE[raw data] --> SILVER[filtered, cleaned data] --> GOLD[business level aggregation]
                        data quality increases as it moves


