Rational database --  which stores structured data or tables 
non-rational database -- which store structured and semi structured data - eg: managoDB, apache cassandra

------------------------------------------------------

data lake [vs] delta lake [vs] lakehouse [vs] data warehouse

data lake - store raw data, support structure, semi structure and un structure data
            eg = ADLS gen2 and amazon s3

delta lake - data lake + reliability like ACID properties, schema enforcement, time travel etc
            eg = delta lake

data warehouse - design for structure data, Optimized for BI & reporting
            Limitation - Expensive and Not good for raw/unstructured data
            eg = Examples: Azure Synapse Analytics ans Snowflake

lakehouse - the system combines best of data lake + delta lake + data warehouse
            eg = Databricks Lakehouse Platform

| Feature       | Data Lake   | Delta Lake         | Data Warehouse     | Lakehouse         |
| ------------- | ----------- | ------------------ | ------------------ | ----------------- |
| Data Type     | All types   | All types          | Structured         | All types         |
| Storage       | Cheap       | Cheap              | Expensive          | Cheap             |
| ACID          | ❌ No       | ✅ Yes            | ✅ Yes             | ✅ Yes           |
| Schema        | ❌ Flexible | ✅ Enforced       | ✅ Strict          | ✅ Enforced      |
| Performance   | ❌ Slower   | ⚡ Better         | ⚡⚡ Very fast    | ⚡⚡ Fast        |
| Use Case      | Raw storage | Reliable data lake | BI / Reporting     | Unified analytics |
| Example Tools | ADLS, S3    | Delta Lake         | Synapse, Snowflake | Databricks        |


